            <title>[LUCENE-1303] BoostingTermQuery&apos;s explanation should be marked as Match even if the payload part negated or zero&apos;ed it</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1303</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Since BTQ multiplies the payload on the score it might return a negative score.&lt;br/&gt;
The explanation should be marked as &quot;Match&quot; otherwise it is not added to container explanations,&lt;br/&gt;
See also in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1302&quot; title=&quot;explain should not mask negative scores&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LUCENE-1302&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-1302&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
